==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mandarining
<hw>Man`da*rin"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Dyeing)</fld> <def>The
process of giving an orange color to goods formed of animal tissue, as
silk or wool, not by coloring matter, but by producing a certain change
in the fiber by the action of dilute nitric acid.</def>
<rj><au>Tomlinson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mandarinism</ent>⟦br⟧
